---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const description = 'Future Canon Tools explains how Vaelinya is being prepared for a future document-based AI assistant that protects canon and supports writers without inventing the world by itself.';
---
<BaseLayout title="Future Canon Tools" description={description}>
  <section class="page-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Future tools</p>
    <h1>Future Canon Tools</h1>
    <p class="lede">Vaelinya is being built as a living world, but not as a loose or careless one.</p>

    <div class="panel">
      <h2>The Vaelinya Canon Oracle</h2>
      <p>As the stories, language, rituals, creatures, maps, and canon notes grow, the project will need a reliable way to search and protect its own material.</p>
      <p>For that reason, Vaelinya is being prepared for a future document-based AI system: the <strong>Vaelinya Canon Oracle</strong>.</p>
      <p>This kind of system is often called RAG, or retrieval-augmented generation. In simple terms, it means an AI assistant answers from selected documents instead of guessing from memory.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="panel">
      <h2>What it will do</h2>
      <p>The Canon Oracle will not invent canon by itself. Its purpose will be to search official Vaelinya documents and help answer questions from the existing world.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>check whether a new idea fits established canon</li>
        <li>help writers find relevant lore before writing</li>
        <li>answer questions about Vaelinyan culture, language, creatures, places, and rituals</li>
        <li>prevent contradictions between stories and worldbuilding notes</li>
        <li>support future teaching materials, guides, and Writer’s Commons resources</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="panel">
      <h2>What matters now</h2>
      <p>For now, the priority is simple: keep the world clear, carefully filed, and human-led.</p>
      <p>The Oracle is a future tool. Vaelinya remains a written world first.</p>
      <div class="link-list">
        <a href="/about/">Back to About Vaelinya</a>
        <a href="/world/">Explore the world</a>
        <a href="/read/">Read the stories</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
